  "texts": [
    "By using these definitions, the authors proved the two Lemmas below.",
    "Lemma 2 (Lemma 4 [18]) Let F(G) = ⟨F 1, F 2,..., F n-k ⟩ be a core sequence of a k-path graph with n vertices.",
    "There is a unique restricted normalized coloring sequence [18]) Let C = ⟨a 1, a 2,..., a n-k-1 ⟩ be a restricted normalized sequence with at most k+1 distinct integers.",
    "C is a coloring sequence of a unique k-path graph with n vertices.C = ⟨c 1, c 2,..., c n-k-1 ⟩ of F(G) with at most k + 1 colors.",
    "Lemma 3 (Lemma 5According to [18], for fixed k, the total number of k-path graphs with n vertices can be obtained asT (n, k) = T (n-1, k-1)+M (n, k)+N (n, k), where T (n -1, k -1)is the number of k-path graphs that has at least one universal vertex; M (n, k) is the number of symmetric k-path graphs without universal vertices and N (n, k) is the number of non-symmetric k-path graphs without universal vertices."
